8) jpa,hibernate,spring jpa

JPA	Choreographer / Dance Blueprint	Tells everyone the rules of the dance (how to map Java objects to DB tables). It doesnâ€™t dance itself.
Hibernate	Professional dancer	Follows the choreography and actually performs the dance (runs SQL, maps objects to tables, handles transactions).
Spring Data JPA	Dance coach / choreographerâ€™s assistant	Makes the dance easier to perform: gives dancers ready-made steps, so you donâ€™t have to teach every move manually (like automatic CRUD, repository methods, pagination).


9) what happens when springbootApplication.run()

- spring creates application context which is a container which can be used to store the beans
- scan of bean
- create and register of the beans
- beans are injected via dependency injection
- autoconfiguraton handles the setup of dependency like tomcat,jackson,spring mvc etc
- Spring Boot starts an embedded server like Tomcat. app is ready to listen to requests.
- Application Ready to Serve Requests

10) Type of beans
- single : throught the request only one bean is shared
- prototype : for every request new bean is created
- session : for every session new bean is created

